{{> welcome-menu active="about"}}

<div class="content box sunny">
    <h1 class="title has-text-link">
        About WeatherTop app
    </h1>
</div>

<div class="box content has-text-centered">
    <h3 class="subtitle is-5">
        How to use this app?
    </h3>
    <div class="box">
        <h4 class="subtitle is-6">
            1. First, you need to register
        </h4>
        <p>After registering, you can log in</p>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://cdn.glitch.global/95d1a9fd-89db-42a3-bf6b-9afea9f0dd2c/register.png?v=1692267657144" alt="how to register">
        </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
        <h4 class="subtitle is-6">
            2. Then, you can start adding weather stations
        </h4>
        <p>A location, latitude and longitude are mandatory</p>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://cdn.glitch.global/95d1a9fd-89db-42a3-bf6b-9afea9f0dd2c/addstation.png?v=1692267639235" alt="how to add a station">
        </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
        <h4 class="subtitle is-6">
            3. You will now see the station you added on the "Dashboard"
        </h4>
        <p>Here you will see the readings for the station (if available), and you can open or destroy the station</p>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://cdn.glitch.global/95d1a9fd-89db-42a3-bf6b-9afea9f0dd2c/newstation.png?v=1692267671353" alt="what a new station looks like">
        </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
        <h4 class="subtitle is-6">
            4. Opening the station will allow you to submit a reading"
        </h4>
        <p>New readings require an input for weather code, temperature, wind speed, wind direction, and pressure</p>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://cdn.glitch.global/95d1a9fd-89db-42a3-bf6b-9afea9f0dd2c/addreading.png?v=1692267614273" alt="how to add a reading">
        </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
        <h4 class="subtitle is-6">
            5. Once a reading has been entered and submitted, the new reading will show on the station"
        </h4>
        <p>Please note that for a trend to appear, a minimum of 3 readings have to be associated with a station</p>
        <figure>
            <img src="https://cdn.glitch.global/95d1a9fd-89db-42a3-bf6b-9afea9f0dd2c/readings.png?v=1692267651779" alt="what readings look like">
        </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
        <h4 class="subtitle is-6">
            6. Enjoy using your weather station and viewing your measurement history!
        </h4>
    </div>
</div>


